This paper discusses the use of lexical semantics in natural language processing, specifically in the context of semantical analyzers such as Boxer or Grail. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
